# =====================================================================
# 301 REDIRECT MAP — for deployment when this site replaces anft.earth
# =====================================================================
#
# PURPOSE: preserve a decade of inbound links and search rankings by
# permanently redirecting replaced WordPress pages to their new
# counterparts. Deploy these rules in the site's .htaccess (Apache) or
# translate to your server's equivalent.
#
# ============================ CRITICAL ===============================
# NOT EVERYTHING GETS REDIRECTED. The new static site deliberately
# LINKS OUT to several anft.earth URLs that are functional systems
# (enrollment listings, directories, maps, the member network page).
# Those URLs must REMAIN LIVE on the WordPress side — redirecting them
# would create redirect loops (new page -> old URL -> new page).
#
# MUST REMAIN LIVE (do NOT redirect these):
#   /training-events/                                  (online-first cohort listings; linked from homepage)
#   /combos/  and everything under it                  (in-person-first cohort pages; linked from training cards)
#   /training-immersions/  and everything under it     (immersion event pages)
#   /forest-therapy-guide-certification/online/        (enrollment; linked from guide-training page)
#   /forest-therapy-guide-certification/in-person/     (enrollment; linked from guide-training page)
#   /healthcare-professional-forest-therapy-training/  (NaM details & walkthrough calls; linked from nature-as-medicine page)
#   /listings/                                         (guide directory; linked from global guide map page)
#   /trails-overview/                                  (trail map; linked from global trail map page)
#   /about-global-network/                             (network join page; linked from membership page)
#   members.anft.earth                                 (member portal subdomain)
#
# If any of the above are later rebuilt inside the new site, update the
# corresponding new-site link FIRST, then add the redirect here.
# =====================================================================

# ------------------ ACTIVE REDIRECTS (safe, no loops) ----------------

# Marketing/overview pages fully replaced by the new site.
# End-anchored so live child pages (/online/, /in-person/) are untouched:
RedirectMatch 301 ^/forest-therapy-guide-certification/$ /relational-forest-therapy-academy--guide-training.html
RedirectMatch 301 ^/guide-certification-process/$ /relational-forest-therapy-academy--guide-training.html
RedirectMatch 301 ^/guide-training-faqs/$ /relational-forest-therapy-academy--guide-training.html
RedirectMatch 301 ^/relational-forest-therapy-course/$ /relational-forest-therapy-academy.html
RedirectMatch 301 ^/certify-your-trail/$ /academy-of-place--trail-certification.html
RedirectMatch 301 ^/become-a-consultant/$ /academy-of-place--consultant-training.html
RedirectMatch 301 ^/contact/$ /contact.html

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# AFTER DEPLOYING: in Google Search Console, submit the new sitemap
# (https://anft.earth/sitemap.xml) and use URL Inspection on a few of
# the redirected old URLs to confirm Google sees the 301s.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# ------------------------- CUSTOM 404 PAGE ---------------------------
# Serve the branded not-found page for any missing URL:
ErrorDocument 404 /404.html
